  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "iATffMMXdsGLOov1VPg7bA7BqH0=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:39.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# operation error index must match the number of prior dispatches\n\nWhen testing reducer errors, the operation index matters:\n\n```typescript\n// First operation dispatched \u2192 index [0]\nconst doc1 = reducer(document, addItem({ id: \"1\", name: \"test\" }));\n\n// Second operation dispatched \u2192 index [1]\nconst doc2 = reducer(doc1, addItem({ id: \"1\", name: \"duplicate\" }));\nexpect(doc2.operations.global[1].error).toBe(\"Duplicate ID\");\n\n// \u274c Wrong \u2014 index [0] is the first (successful) operation\nexpect(doc2.operations.global[0].error).toBe(\"Duplicate ID\");\n```\n\nThe index corresponds to the total number of operations dispatched, not the number of errors. Since [[operation errors are recorded on operations not thrown to callers]], every dispatch (successful or failed) produces an operation at the next index.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[reducer patterns]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:39.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:39.000Z"
    }
  },
